B%20Johnny%20Nunez%2FWireImage%3B%20KMazur%2FWireImage%20for%20Interscope%20Records%3B%20Lynn%20Goldsmith%2FCorbis%2FVCG%2FGetty%3B%20Dakarai%20Akil%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incredible%20saga%20of%20the%20Henchmen%20brothers%2C%20hip-hop's%20forgotten%20moguls%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20in%20eight%20years%20that%20Mario%20Rosemond%20heard%20his%20name%2C%20it%20filled%20him%20with%20terror.%20Almost%20as%20much%20as%20the%20men%20surrounding%20him%20with%20machine%20guns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20March%202019%2C%20and%20Rosemond%20was%20living%20in%20Mexico%20under%20an%20assumed%20identity.%20Born%20in%20Haiti%20and%20tossed%20out%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Brooklyn%20as%20a%20teenager%2C%20he%20was%20on%20the%20run%20from%20the%20FBI%2C%20for%20his%20role%20in%20a%20cocaine-trafficking%20empire%20run%20by%20his%20younger%20brother%2C%20Jimmy.%20But%20the%20Rosemond%20brothers%20were%20no%20ordinary%20hustlers.%20As%20founders%20of%20Henchmen%20Entertainment%2C%20rap's%20most%20notorious%20management%20firm%2C%20Jimmy%20and%20Mario%20had%20made%20millions%20the%20legit%20way%3A%20by%20deftly%20cultivating%20artists%20such%20as%20The%20Game%2C%20Salt-N-Pepa%2C%20Akon%2C%20Sean%20Kingston%2C%20and%20Gucci%20Mane.%20During%20their%20meteoric%20rise%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20Mario%20had%20kept%20a%20low%20profile%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street-trained%20numbers%20guy%20who%20quietly%20managed%20the%20company's%20fortunes.%20Jimmy%2C%20five%20years%20younger%2C%20served%20as%20Henchmen's%20flashy%20and%20intimidating%20front%20man%2C%20the%20self-described%20%26quot%3Bgangster%20manager%26quot%3B%20of%20hip-hop.%20%26quot%3BThey%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20go%20from%20the%20streets%20to%20the%20boardrooms%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Skee%2C%20one%20of%20rap's%20most%20influential%20producers%20and%20DJs.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20that%20respect.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20according%20to%20the%20Feds%2C%20Jimmy%20never%20left%20the%20streets%20at%20all.%20%26quot%3BRosemond%20styled%20himself%20a%20hip%20hop%20mogul%2C%20bringing%20the%20music%20of%20the%20streets%20to%20a%20wider%20audience%20and%20expanding%20opportunities%20of%20artists%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20Justice%20Department%20put%20it.%20%26quot%3BIn%20reality%2C%20his%20image%20as%20a%20music%20impresario%20was%20a%20cover%20for%20the%20real%20Jimmy%20Rosemond%20%E2%80%94%20a%20thug%20in%20a%20suit%20who%20flooded%20those%20same%20streets%20with%20cocaine%2C%20and%20shuttled%20drugs%20and%20money%20from%20coast%20to%20coast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArrested%20in%202011%2C%20Jimmy%20was%20convicted%20of%20running%20a%20massive%20drug%20empire%20and%20of%20ordering%20the%20murder%20of%20Lowell%20%26quot%3BLodi%20Mack%26quot%3B%20Fletcher%2C%20an%20associate%20of%2050%20Cent%20who%20was%20gunned%20down%20in%20the%20Bronx.%20Some%20in%20the%20rap%20world%20also%20suspected%20him%20of%20masterminding%20the%201994%20shooting%20of%20Tupac%20Shakur%20at%20Quad%20Studios%2C%20igniting%20the%20bicoastal%20rap%20feud%20that%20led%20to%20the%20murders%20of%20both%20Tupac%20and%20Biggie%20Smalls.%20Now%20serving%20two%20life%20sentences%20in%20federal%20prison%2C%20Jimmy%20continues%20to%20maintain%20his%20innocence%2C%20claiming%20he%20served%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bfall%20guy%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20drugs%20and%20violence%20that%20plagued%20the%20music%20industry.%20%26quot%3BThat%20dark%20force%20that%20we%20grew%20up%20on%2C%20that%20Joker%20character%2C%20that%20nemesis%20of%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me%20on%20a%20recent%20call%20from%20prison.%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20I%20became%20that%20in%20the%20music%20business%2C%20and%20to%20reporters%2C%20and%20eventually%20to%20prosecutors%20who%20felt%20they%20needed%20to%20rid%20the%20business%20of%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jimmy%20Henchman%20getting%20arrested%20by%20DEA%20officers.%20A%20sketch%20of%20his%20trial.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c29189cf077800196547ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22906%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJimmy%20Rosemond%20was%20arrested%20in%202011%20and%20received%20two%20life%20sentences%20on%20charges%20of%20drug%20running%20and%20murder%20for%20hire.%3Cp%3EAP%20Newsroom%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Jimmy's%20arrest%20that%20drove%20Mario%20to%20flee%20to%20Mexico.%20Faced%20with%20having%20to%20testify%20against%20his%20brother%2C%20Rosemond%20pulled%20a%20Saul%20Goodman.%20He%20paid%20%2450%2C000%20to%20be%20smuggled%20down%20to%20Cuernavaca%2C%20where%20he%20adopted%20a%20new%20identity%3A%20Tommy%20Davis.%20Leaving%20behind%20his%20family%20and%20friends%2C%20he%20spent%20eight%20years%20living%20with%20%26quot%3Bmy%20head%20on%20a%20swivel%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Mario%20puts%20it%2C%20always%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20anyone%20who%20might%20recognize%20him.%20He%20kept%20a%20low%20profile.%20He%20learned%20Spanish%2C%20steered%20clear%20of%20serious%20relationships%2C%20and%20went%20to%20church%20on%20Sundays.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20trusting%20nobody%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20help%20that%20Cuernavaca%20had%20become%20a%20battleground%2C%20with%20one%20of%20Mexico's%20fiercest%20cartels%20erupting%20in%20an%20internal%20war.%20Driving%20to%20the%20gym%2C%20Rosemond%20would%20pass%20the%20corpse%20of%20a%20freshly%20butchered%20gangster%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20road.%20A%20friend%20he%20knew%20got%20shot%20dead%20by%20the%20cartel%2C%20and%20his%20roommate%2C%20a%20steroid-jacked%20Colombian%2C%20had%20been%20kidnapped%20for%20three%20days%20before%20managing%20to%20escape.%20It%20was%20a%20dangerous%20place%20to%20be%20living%20on%20the%20lam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moment%20Rosemond's%20past%20caught%20up%20with%20him%20felt%20nightmarishly%20surreal.%20He%20was%20doing%20his%20laundry%20in%20the%20courtyard%20of%20his%20apartment%20building%20when%20he%20spotted%20five%20armed%20men%20climbing%20the%20fence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20looking%20for%20Mario%20Rosemond%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20them%20told%20him%20in%20English.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EYo%20no%20s%C3%A9%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20stammered%20in%20Spanish.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EMi%20nombre%20es%20Tommy%20Davis%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20they%20threw%20a%20bag%20over%20his%20head%2C%20and%20everything%20went%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20four%20years%20later%2C%20Rosemond's%20life%20still%20hangs%20in%20the%20balance.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20hard%20even%20speaking%20on%20it%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20endgame%20is.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20talking%20over%20breakfast%20at%20a%20Friendly's%20near%20Rahway%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20a%20universe%20away%20from%20Rosemond's%20takedown%20in%20Cuernavaca.%20At%20age%2064%2C%20dressed%20in%20blue%20jeans%20and%20a%20blue%20polo%2C%20he%20comes%20across%20as%20less%20urban%20gangster%20than%20suburban%20grandad.%20It's%20a%20status%20he%20has%20earned%20by%20spending%20his%20days%20babysitting%20his%202-year-old%20grandson.%20The%20only%20sign%20of%20his%20hip-hop%20past%20are%20the%20tattoos%20on%20his%20right%20arm%20memorializing%20his%20late%20mother%20and%20sister.%20Whatever%20choices%20he%20has%20made%20in%20life%2C%20he%20says%2C%20it%20was%20always%20his%20family%20that%20drove%20him.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20too%20many%20people%20in%20my%20circle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20family.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20as%20he%20awaits%20sentencing%20for%20participating%20in%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20distribute%20cocaine%2C%20he's%20sharing%20his%20incredible%20saga%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20from%20his%20meteoric%20rise%20in%20Brooklyn%20to%20his%20inglorious%20fall%20in%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jimmy%20Henchman%20and%20Mario%20Henchman%20with%20the%20family.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c1475535e9130019c663c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJimmy%20(far%20left)%20and%20his%20son%20Jimmy%20Jr.%20with%20Mario%20(far%20right)%20and%20their%20mother%2C%20Andrea.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20too%20many%20people%20in%20my%20circle%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20family.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leeann%20Hellijas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMario's%20working-class%20parents%20migrated%20from%20Port-au-Prince%20to%20New%20York%20City%20when%20he%20was%207.%20Constantin%20was%20a%20carpenter%3B%20Andrea%20got%20work%20as%20a%20nurse.%20%26quot%3BLike%20every%20immigrant%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20wanted%20a%20better%20life.%26quot%3B%20The%20family%20settled%20in%20Vanderveer%20Estates%2C%20a%20housing%20project%20of%2059%20rundown%20buildings%20that%20sprawled%20across%2030%20acres%20of%20East%20Flatbush.%20Quiet%20and%20intellectual%2C%20Mario%20tried%20to%20provide%20an%20example%20for%20his%20four%20younger%20siblings%2C%20especially%20Jimmy.%20But%20their%20home%20life%20was%20troubled.%20Constantin%2C%20an%20abusive%20womanizer%2C%20%26quot%3Bwould%20beat%20us%20with%20anything%20and%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20recalls.%20At%20age%2016%2C%20after%20Mario%20stepped%20in%20to%20stop%20his%20father%20from%20assaulting%20his%20mother%2C%20Constantin%20told%20him%20there%20wasn't%20room%20for%20two%20grown%20men%20in%20the%20house%20and%20threw%20him%20out.%20%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20worked%20hard%20to%20keep%20us%20out%20of%20the%20street%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%2C%20you%20know%2C%20the%20street%20always%20come%20and%20get%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario%20tried%20street%20life%20himself%2C%20joining%20a%20gang%20of%20petty%20thieves%20called%20the%20Jolly%20Stompers.%20But%20after%20a%20high-school%20guidance%20counselor%20helped%20him%20secure%20a%20Wall%20Street%20internship%2C%20Mario%20learned%20how%20to%20build%20a%20fortune%20the%20old-fashioned%20way.%20%26quot%3BLegal%20money%2C%20not%20having%20to%20worry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20learned%20how%20people%20really%20got%20rich.%26quot%3B%20The%20Masters%20of%20the%20Universe%2C%20he%20realized%2C%20did%20it%20by%20keeping%20a%20low%20profile.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20in%20the%20background%2C%20nobody%20knows%20about%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20know%20that%20you're%20actually%20running%20things.%20They%20don't%20know%20that%20you're%20watching%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20Mario%20worked%20to%20ascend%20the%20ranks%20of%20Wall%20Street%20and%20started%20a%20family%20of%20his%20own%2C%20Jimmy%20remained%20behind%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20where%20he%20hung%20out%20in%20the%20projects.%20With%20his%20father%20out%20of%20the%20picture%20and%20his%20mother%20working%20two%20jobs%2C%20Jimmy%20%26quot%3Bhad%20to%20fend%20for%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20no%20guardianship%2C%20so%20the%20streets%20is%20what%20adopted%20me.%26quot%3B%20At%2010%2C%20he%20fell%20in%20with%20a%20local%20Jamaican%20gang%20called%20the%20Untouchables.%20At%2013%2C%20he%20owned%20his%20first%20gun.%20At%2018%2C%20he%20landed%20in%20Rikers%20Island%20on%20a%20firearm%20charge.%20Jimmy%20considered%20Rikers%20%26quot%3Bgladiator%20school.%26quot%3B%20He%20studied%20the%20Black%20Panthers%2C%20converted%20to%20Islam%2C%20and%20learned%20his%20trade%20from%20the%20city's%20most%20experienced%20drug%20dealers.%20Despite%20%26quot%3Beverything%20that%20I%20know%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20is%20the%20only%20family%20I%20had.%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20worked%20his%20way%20up%20to%20become%2C%20as%20he%20later%20boasted%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20drug%20dealer%20in%20Brooklyn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201992%2C%20after%20the%20cops%20busted%20down%20his%20door%20looking%20for%20drugs%2C%20Jimmy%20approached%20his%20brother%20Mario%20with%20a%20proposition%3A%20%3Cem%3ELet's%20start%20a%20music-management%20company%3C%2Fem%3E.%20For%20Jimmy%2C%20as%20he%20later%20put%20it%2C%20music%20was%20a%20way%20to%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bhideout%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20drug%20money.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20know%20anything%20about%20the%20music%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%20about%20the%20music%20business.%20But%20one%20of%20the%20fascinations%20of%20being%20a%20gangster%20or%20a%20drug%20dealer%20is%20you%20want%20to%20rub%20shoulders%20with%20guys%20who%20have%20money%2C%20or%20guys%20of%20your%20stature%2C%20and%20you%20look%20at%20entertainers%20as%20those%20guys.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222752%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jimmy%20Henchmen%20of%20Henchmen%20Entertainment%20and%20The%20Game.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c147e71e871c00191b0535%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222064%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJimmy%20(left)%20with%20his%20client%2C%20The%20Game.%20He%20got%20into%20the%20music%20business%2C%20he%20says%2C%20to%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bhideout%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20drug%20money.%3Cp%3EJohnny%20Nunez%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJimmy%20was%20hitting%20up%20his%20brother%20at%20a%20vulnerable%20moment.%20Mario%20was%20just%20out%20of%20Rikers%20himself%2C%20where%20he%20was%20sentenced%20to%20spend%20every%20weekend%20for%2018%20months%20for%20%E2%80%94%20unwittingly%2C%20he%20claims%20%E2%80%94%20cashing%20stolen%20checks%20for%20a%20friend.%20Out%20of%20a%20job%20and%20unemployable%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20with%20a%20young%20daughter%20to%20support%2C%20Mario%20was%20a%20sharp-enough%20businessman%20to%20spot%20an%20opportunity.%20Plus%20he%20loved%20music%2C%20and%20had%20been%20DJing%20at%20clubs%20under%20the%20name%20Mr.%20Slick.%20With%20the%20popularity%20of%20rap%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20emerging%20artists%20and%20producers%20needed%20someone%20to%20represent%20them%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20who%20could%20navigate%20the%20treacherous%20waters%20of%20the%20music%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20gather%20all%20the%20top%20talent%20in%20one%20place%2C%20Jimmy%20and%20Mario%20organized%20a%20conference%20called%20%26quot%3BHow%20Can%20I%20Be%20Down%3F%26quot%3B%20Held%20in%20Miami%20Beach%20in%201992%2C%20the%20event%20attracted%20a%20Who's%20Who%20of%20hip-hop's%20early%20moguls%3A%20Russell%20Simmons%2C%20Benny%20Medina%2C%20Lyor%20Cohen%2C%20Chris%20Lighty%2C%20Mona%20Scott.%20While%20Jimmy%20worked%20the%20crowd%2C%20Mario%20practiced%20the%20skill%20he%20had%20learned%20on%20Wall%20Street.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20just%20a%20fly%20on%20the%20wall%2C%20so%20no%20one%20really%20pays%20attention%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalls.%20%26quot%3BAs%20opposed%20to%20my%20brother%2C%20he%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20front%20man.%20That's%20why%20in%20the%20music%20business%20we%20worked%20so%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20fall%2C%20the%20brothers%20proved%20their%20prowess%20by%20engineering%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20rap%20songs%20of%20the%20year.%20Salt-N-Pepa%2C%20the%20pioneering%20female%20rap%20trio%20from%20New%20York%2C%20were%20on%20their%20fourth%20record%20and%20in%20need%20of%20a%20hit%20when%20Jimmy%20hooked%20them%20up%20with%20Mark%20Sparks%2C%20a%20producer%20friend.%20Jimmy%20had%20zero%20experience%20in%20music%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20matter.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20young%20enough%20to%20where%20I%20trusted%20my%20ears%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20Released%20in%20September%201993%2C%20the%20resulting%20single%2C%20%26quot%3BShoop%2C%26quot%3B%20became%20a%20runaway%20hit%2C%20topping%20the%20rap%20charts%20and%20going%20gold%20in%20only%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222285%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20band%20Salt%20n'%20Pepper.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c14ca49440b70019265155%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221714%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20brothers%20engineered%20their%20first%20hit%3A%20Salt-N-Pepa's%201993%20single%20%26quot%3BShoop.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EPaul%20Bergen%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brothers%20quickly%20followed%20up%20with%20another%20hit%2C%20%26quot%3BTell%20Me%2C%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20R%26amp%3BB%20duo%20Groove%20Theory.%20The%20band's%20cofounder%20Bryce%20Wilson%20remembers%20Jimmy%20as%20a%20small%2C%20geeky%20guy%20in%20glasses.%20%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20present%20himself%20as%20a%20gangster.%20Jimmy%20was%20a%20nerd%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilson%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20he%20was%20extremely%20loyal%20and%20extremely%20unselfish%20and%20would%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20things%20happen.%26quot%3B%20He%20was%20also%20a%20canny%20businessman.%20Jimmy%20hit%20on%20a%20groundbreaking%20idea%3A%20He%20and%20Mario%20would%20sign%20rap%20producers%20instead%20of%20artists%20and%20make%20them%20stars%20in%20their%20own%20right.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20understood%20was%20the%20real%20estate%20of%20the%20music%2C%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20says.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20else%20you're%20selling%20in%20music%20is%20intangible%20but%20the%20publishing.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20they%20needed%20for%20their%20management%20company%20was%20a%20name.%20Jimmy%20wanted%20something%20that%20evoked%20his%20personal%20history%2C%20his%20move%20from%20Rikers%20to%20rap.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20bringing%20the%20street%20into%20the%20music%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says.%20The%20kid%20who%20fought%20his%20way%20out%20of%20the%20projects%20rebranded%20himself%20as%20Jimmy%20Henchman%2C%20and%20he%20dubbed%20their%20new%20enterprise%20Henchmen%20Entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJimmy%20and%20Mario%20have%20a%20lot%20in%20common%3A%20intelligence%2C%20loyalty%20to%20those%20who%20deserve%20it%2C%20no%20time%20for%20those%20who%20don't.%20They%20also%20share%20a%20way%20of%20speaking%2C%20punctuating%20their%20comments%20with%20the%20occasional%20%3Cem%3Emmm-hmm%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20if%20preaching%20to%20themselves%2C%20a%20looping%20call%20and%20response.%20When%20I%20ask%20Jimmy%20what%20he%20learned%20from%20the%20street%20that%20he%20took%20into%20the%20music%20business%2C%20the%20convicted%20drug%20dealer%20delivers%20a%20gospel%20on%20integrity.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20known%20to%20be%20a%20thief%2C%20that's%20how%20they're%20gonna%20deal%20with%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20known%20to%20be%20trustworthy%2C%20they%20get%20to%20trust%20in%20you%20more.%20So%20it%20applied%20the%20same%20way%20in%20the%20music%20business.%20People%20buy%20into%20the%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Jimmy%20as%20the%20public-facing%20godfather%20and%20Mario%20the%20calculating%20consigliere%2C%20the%20brothers%20styled%20themselves%20as%20hip-hop%20Corleones.%20Adopting%20the%20name%20Henchman%20not%20only%20bolstered%20Jimmy's%20reputation%20but%20also%20helped%20him%20dodge%20the%20cops%2C%20who%20were%20after%20him%20on%20gun%20charges.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20know%20where%20he%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20recalls%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20he's%20Jimmy%20Henchman%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%2015%20or%20so%20employees%20also%20used%20the%20Henchman%20name%2C%20even%20printing%20it%20on%20their%20business%20cards.%20Mohammed%20%26quot%3BTef%26quot%3B%20Stewart%2C%20a%20friend%20from%20Brooklyn%20who%20joined%20the%20team%2C%20became%20Tef%20Henchman%2C%20a%20title%20he%20wore%20with%20the%20same%20pride%20he%20took%20in%20Jimmy.%20%26quot%3BHenchman%20was%20his%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20later%20testified%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20it%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20under%20him.%26quot%3B%20The%20new%20moniker%20helped%20them%20get%20into%20clubs%2C%20score%20meetings%2C%20and%20ward%20off%20trouble.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20a%20free%20pass%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20everybody%20knew%20we%20had%20muscle.%26quot%3B%20Only%20one%20member%20of%20the%20crew%20refused%20to%20use%20the%20new%20handle%3A%20Mario.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20no%20part%20of%20that%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20He%20had%20a%20motivation%20for%20playing%20it%20safe.%20He%20wanted%20to%20protect%20his%2012-year-old%20daughter%2C%20who%20was%20living%20with%20his%20ex-wife%20in%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20November%2030%2C%201994%2C%20the%20Henchmen%20name%20became%20etched%20into%20the%20history%20of%20hip-hop.%20Jimmy%20had%20agreed%20to%20pay%20%2415%2C000%20to%20have%20the%20industry's%20hottest%20rapper%2C%20Tupac%20Shakur%2C%20stop%20by%20Quad%20Studios%20in%20New%20York%20and%20record%20a%20track%20with%20the%20Henchmen%20artist%20Little%20Shawn.%20Mario%20had%20known%20Tupac%20since%20the%20'80s%20and%20felt%20a%20kinship%20with%20the%20introspective%20young%20artist.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20down%20to%20earth%2C%20a%20quiet%2C%20quiet%2C%20quiet%20dude%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says.%20%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20even%20have%20any%20bodyguards.%20He%20would%20be%20by%20himself.%20He%20was%20a%20regular%20kid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20night%2C%20Mario%20recalls%2C%20he%20was%20back%20at%20Henchmen's%20headquarters%2C%20opting%20for%20the%20quietude%20of%20the%20office%20over%20the%20scene%20at%20the%20studio.%20Then%20his%20phone%20rang.%20It%20was%20Jimmy%2C%20sounding%20agitated.%20Tupac%20was%20late%2C%20and%20with%20the%20rap%20stars%20Puff%20Daddy%20and%20Biggie%20Smalls%20milling%20around%20the%20studio%2C%20Jimmy%20was%20losing%20not%20only%20time%20and%20money%20but%20something%20even%20more%20dangerous%3A%20face.%20Jimmy%20wanted%20Mario%20to%20track%20down%20his%20old%20friend%20and%20get%20him%20to%20the%20studio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario%20called%20Tupac.%20%26quot%3BYo%2C%20dude%2C%20where%20you%20at%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%20Pac%20said%20he%20was%20uptown%20making%20drops%20with%20a%20DJ%2C%20but%20promised%20to%20show%20up%20for%20the%20studio%20gig.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20gonna%20be%20there%2C%20man%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20promised%20Mario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20hours%20later%2C%20Mario%20got%20another%2C%20more%20alarming%20call%20from%20his%20brother.%20%26quot%3BYo%2C%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPac%20just%20got%20shot!%26quot%3B%20Suspicion%20immediately%20fell%20on%20the%20Henchmen%20brothers.%20Tupac's%20manager%2C%20Freddie%20Moore%2C%20called%20Mario%20and%20accused%20him%20and%20Jimmy%20of%20setting%20Tupac%20up.%20%26quot%3BYo%2C%20somebody%20shot%20my%20man%20five%20times%20and%20y'all%20guys%20didn't%20know%20about%20it%3F!%26quot%3B%20Moore%20shouted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222404%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rappers%20B.I.G.%20and%20Tupac%20Shakur%20pose%20for%20a%20portrait%20at%20Club%20Amazon%20on%20July%2023%2C%201993%20in%20New%20York%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c2a45bcf07780019656da0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221803%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOn%20the%20night%20Tupac%20was%20shot%20in%201994%2C%20he%20was%20supposed%20to%20record%20a%20track%20with%20the%20Henchmen%20artist%20Little%20Shawn.%3Cp%3EAl%20Pereira%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDude%2C%20do%20me%20a%20favor%20and%20think%20about%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20replied.%20%26quot%3B'Cause%20me%2C%20I%20start%20trying%20to%20think%20logic%3A%20If%20we%20wanted%20him%20dead%20or%20if%20we%20wanted%20him%20hurt%2C%20wouldn't%20we%20have%20done%20the%20record%20first%3F%20If%20he's%20dead%2C%20that%20would've%20been%20the%20last%20song.%20You%20know%2C%20my%20artist%20would%20be%20blowing%20the%20fuck%20up!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20found%20no%20evidence%20linking%20Jimmy%20to%20Tupac's%20shooting%2C%20which%20ignited%20a%20deadly%20war%20between%20the%20East%20Coast%20and%20West%20Coast%20branches%20of%20rap.%20And%20Jimmy%20continues%20to%20claim%2C%20against%20all%20evidence%3Cstrong%3E%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20that%20Tupac%20accidentally%20shot%20himself%20with%20his%20own%20gun.%20%26quot%3BI%20look%20guilty%20as%20fuck%20to%20anybody%20who's%20standing%20around%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20guy%20never%20was%20shot%20up%20%E2%80%94%20he%20shot%20himself.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20with%20the%20police%20looking%20for%20him%20on%20gun%20charges%2C%20Jimmy%20wasn't%20taking%20any%20chances.%20As%20Tupac%20lay%20bleeding%20in%20the%20lobby%20of%20the%20studio%2C%20Jimmy%20slipped%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario%20is%20cagier%20about%20Jimmy's%20involvement%20in%20the%20shooting.%20%26quot%3BIf%20he%20did%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20would%20have%20been%20stupid.%26quot%3B%20When%20I%20ask%20Mario%20if%20he%20thinks%20Jimmy%20is%20innocent%2C%20he%20laughs.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20say%20he's%20innocent%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20saying%20I%20believe%20he's%20innocent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20after%20the%20Tupac%20shooting%2C%20Mario%20was%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Plainfield%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20when%20the%20police%20came%20crashing%20through%20the%20door%2C%20guns%20drawn.%20They%20were%20looking%20for%20Jimmy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvoiding%20drama%20is%20what%20had%20driven%20Mario%20from%20Brooklyn%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20But%20the%20streets%20had%20followed%20him%20to%20the%20suburbs.%20Luckily%2C%20his%20daughter%20wasn't%20there%20to%20see%20the%20cops%20raid%20his%20home%2C%20looking%20for%20her%20uncle.%20The%20experience%20left%20Mario%20more%20resolved%20than%20ever%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20his%20brother's%20affairs.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20that%20experience%2C%20I%20stay%20squeaky%20clean%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20insists.%20%26quot%3B'Cause%20that%20would%20put%20my%20daughter%20and%20family%20in%20danger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20rap%20community%2C%20Tupac's%20shooting%20only%20served%20to%20burnish%20Jimmy's%20reputation%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20after%20Pac%20recorded%20the%20diss%20track%20%26quot%3BAgainst%20All%20Odds%2C%26quot%3B%20vowing%20%26quot%3Bto%20pay%20back%20Jimmy%20Henchman%20in%20due%20time.%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Jimmy%20was%20thrilled.%20%26quot%3BHe%20puts%20me%20in%20that%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20what%20give%20me%20notoriety.%26quot%3B%20But%20Mario%20was%20far%20from%20pleased.%20%26quot%3BIt%20made%20Jimmy%20more%20famous%2C%20and%20for%20him%2C%20he%20loves%20that%2C%20right%3F%20For%20me%2C%20I%20hate%20it%2C%20because%20now%20it%20brings%20more%20light%20to%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20gun%20charges%20still%20looming%2C%20Jimmy%20began%20working%20out%20of%20his%20car%20to%20evade%20the%20police.%20%26quot%3BMario%20was%20in%20the%20office%2C%20so%20I%20was%20able%20to%20move%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20With%20more%20clients%2C%20more%20hits%2C%20and%20more%20money%20pouring%20in%2C%20the%20brothers%20made%20themselves%20indispensable%20to%20those%20around%20them.%20%26quot%3BFlush%20with%20cash%2C%20we%20was%20able%20to%20do%20things%20for%20folks%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says.%20With%20their%20reputation%20growing%2C%20they%20began%20attracting%20more%20and%20more%20top%20stars%2C%20from%20Brandy%20to%20Junior%20Mafia.%20They'd%20make%20deals%2C%20settle%20beefs%2C%20lend%20money%20with%20interest.%20When%20I%20ask%20Mario%20what%20happened%20when%20someone%20didn't%20make%20a%20payment%2C%20he%20dismisses%20the%20idea%20as%20unthinkable.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20always%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Jimmy%20could%20run%20for%20only%20so%20long.%20In%201996%20he%20was%20arrested%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20sent%20to%20prison.%20Mario%20kept%20Henchmen%20running%20while%20Jimmy%20was%20behind%20bars%2C%20but%20by%20the%20time%20his%20brother%20got%20released%20three%20years%20later%2C%20he%20felt%20increasingly%20concerned.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20hot%20up%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BMy%20brother%2C%20some%20of%20the%20moves%20he%20was%20making%20at%20that%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20necessarily%20agree.%20Now%2C%20more%20so%20than%20ever%2C%20the%20street%20is%20definitely%20in%20the%20office.%26quot%3B%20To%20protect%20his%20family%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20put%20some%20distance%20between%20himself%20and%20his%20brother.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20gonna%20go%20to%20the%20West%20Coast%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Jimmy.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20gonna%20start%20my%20own%20thing.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2043%2C%20Mario%20moved%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20built%20a%20new%20life%20far%20from%20the%20troubles%20back%20home.%20He%20started%20an%20adult-film%20company%20called%20Joy%20Ride%20(%26quot%3Bit%20was%20just%20as%20a%20business%20thing%26quot%3B)%2C%20bought%20a%20palatial%20house%20in%20the%20Hollywood%20Hills%2C%20and%20started%20a%20new%20family.%20For%20a%20guy%20who%20always%20wanted%20to%20live%20the%20quiet%20life%2C%20it%20felt%20as%20if%20he%20had%20finally%20found%20some%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20in%20New%20York%2C%20Jimmy%20didn't%20stray%20far%20from%20the%20streets.%20Through%20his%20management%20company%20%C2%AD%E2%80%94%20now%20called%20Czar%20Entertainment%20%E2%80%94%20he%20continued%20to%20manage%20top%20artists.%20He%20brokered%20a%20boxing%20match%20between%20Mike%20Tyson%20and%20Lennox%20Lewis%20that%20became%20the%20highest-grossing%20bout%20in%20history%2C%20with%20over%20%24100%20million%20in%20revenue.%20He%20even%20branched%20out%20into%20politics%2C%20holding%20a%20free%20concert%20in%20Haiti%20with%20Wyclef%20Jean%20and%20Akon%20to%20raise%20awareness%20about%20the%20country's%20plight.%20But%20the%20generosity%20came%20with%20a%20price.%20%26quot%3BJimmy%20was%20always%20there%20for%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Garland%20%26quot%3BGhetto%26quot%3B%20Cyrus%2C%20who%20ran%20Czar's%20record%20distribution%20in%20the%20South.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20just%20a%20guy%20that%20you%20couldn't%20cross.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Port-au-Prince%2C%20HAITI%3A%20Haitian-American%20rapper%20Wiclef%20Jean%20is%20greeted%20by%20fans%2002%20March%202006%20in%20the%20Cite%20Soleil%20slum%20of%20Port-au-Prince.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c14b9b42834d00193e2b47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJimmy%20organized%20a%20free%20concert%20for%20Haiti%20with%20Wyclef%20Jean.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20always%20there%20for%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20employee%20recalled.%3Cp%3ETHONY%20BELIZAIRE%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJimmy's%20tough-guy%20approach%20to%20the%20music%20industry%20erupted%20into%20open%20violence%20when%20he%20signed%20one%20of%20his%20biggest%20artists%3A%20The%20Game.%20A%20member%20of%20G-Unit%2C%20the%20pioneering%20hip-hop%20group%20that%20included%20a%20young%2050%20Cent%2C%20The%20Game%20had%20ties%20to%20Violator%20Management%2C%20a%20rival%20music%20company%20whose%20offices%20happened%20to%20be%20directly%20across%20from%20Czar's%20on%20West%2025th%20Street.%20Violator%20had%20a%20powerhouse%20roster%2C%20including%20Mariah%20Carey%2C%20LL%20Cool%20J%2C%20and%20Missy%20Elliott%2C%20and%20it%20didn't%20take%20The%20Game's%20defection%20lightly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202005%2C%20when%2050%20Cent%20went%20on%20Hot%2097%20radio%20to%20throw%20The%20Game%20out%20of%20his%20group%20and%20dismiss%20him%20as%20%26quot%3Bgone%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20outraged%20Jimmy%20dispatched%20The%20Game%20and%20the%20Henchmen%20soldier%20Tef%20Stewart%20to%20the%20station%20with%20a%20small%20crew%2C%20according%20to%20Stewart.%20When%20they%20arrived%2C%20they%20were%20greeted%20with%20gunshots.%20The%20two%20sides%20clashed%20again%20the%20following%20year%20at%20the%20annual%20Mixtape%20Awards%20at%20the%20Apollo%20Theater%20in%20Harlem.%20As%20Jimmy%20fled%20the%20scene%2C%20one%20of%20his%20soldiers%20shot%20up%20a%20white%20Bentley%20belonging%20to%20a%20member%20of%20G-Unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%20March%202007%2C%20a%20G-Unit%20associate%20named%20Lowell%20%26quot%3BLodi%20Mack%26quot%3B%20Fletcher%20took%20the%20feud%20too%20far.%20As%20he%20was%20leaving%20Violator's%20office%2C%20Fletcher%20spotted%20a%2014-year-old%20boy%20wearing%20a%20Czar%20sweatshirt%20outside%20Jimmy's%20office.%20Racing%20across%20the%20street%2C%20he%20pushed%20the%20kid%20against%20a%20wall%2C%20slapped%20him%2C%20and%20threatened%20him%20with%20a%20gun.%20The%20boy%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20Jimmy%20Rosemond%20Jr.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20got%20the%20news%2C%20Jimmy%20Sr.%20was%20enraged.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20couldn't%20believe%20somebody%20would%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20kid%20was%20only%2014%2C%20he%20looked%20like%20he%20was%2012.%20Then%20I%20found%20out%20it%20was%20these%20clowns.%20They%20crossed%20the%20line%20with%20my%20son.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Mario%20learned%20what%20had%20happened%2C%20he%20urged%20Jimmy%20to%20stay%20cool.%20%26quot%3BI%20passed%20word%20that%20he%20need%20to%20chill%20on%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalls.%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20him%20revenge%20is%20best%20served%20when%20it's%20cold.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFletcher%20was%20sent%20to%20prison%20for%20assault%20and%20endangering%20a%20child%2C%20but%20that%20didn't%20satisfy%20Jimmy.%20War%20broke%20out%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20New%20York.%20Tef%20Stewart's%20barbershop%20was%20burned%20down.%20The%20Henchmen%20suspected%20a%20G-Unit%20associate.%20Stewart%20later%20testified%20that%20he%20and%20others%20in%20Jimmy's%20crew%20bombed%20the%20associate's%20bulletproof%20truck%20with%20Molotov%20cocktails.%20Then%2C%20in%202009%2C%20Fletcher%20was%20released%20from%20prison%20for%20the%20assault%20on%20Jimmy's%20son.%20Two%20weeks%20later%2C%20as%20he%20stepped%20off%20a%20train%20in%20the%20Bronx%2C%20someone%20burst%20out%20of%20the%20shadows%20and%20gunned%20him%20down%2C%20shooting%20him%20five%20times%20in%20the%20back%20with%20a%20.22-caliber%20handgun.%20The%20feud%20over%20Jimmy's%20music%20business%20had%20turned%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20need%20you%20to%20help%20me%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20told%20Mario.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20spring%20of%202011%2C%20and%20Jimmy%20had%20called%20his%20big%20brother%20in%20distress.%20By%20then%2C%20Jimmy%20was%20allegedly%20the%20biggest%20drug%20trafficker%20in%20the%20music%20business.%20With%20a%20dozen%20underlings%20at%20his%20command%2C%20he%20ran%20what%20the%20Feds%20later%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20large%20bicoastal%20narcotics-trafficking%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20moving%20thousands%20of%20pounds%20of%20coke.%20Now%2C%20the%20lieutenant%20who%20ran%20the%20operation%2C%20Khalil%20Abdullah%2C%20had%20been%20arrested%2C%20and%20Jimmy%20wanted%20Mario%20to%20make%20sure%20a%20coming%20payment%20got%20handled.%20%26quot%3BHe%20could%20only%20trust%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20money%2C%20lots%20of%20money%2C%20is%20coming%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECzar%20Entertainment%20had%20become%20both%20a%20nexus%20and%20a%20cover%20for%20the%20trafficking%20enterprise.%20Cocaine%20would%20be%20wrapped%20in%20plastic%2C%20slathered%20in%20mustard%2C%20packed%20in%20musical%20equipment%20boxes%2C%20and%20sent%20from%20Los%20Angeles%20to%20a%20rehearsal%20studio%20in%20New%20York.%20Once%20the%20drugs%20were%20retrieved%2C%20the%20equipment%20boxes%20would%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20LA%2C%20loaded%20with%20millions%20in%20cash.%20Jimmy%20and%20his%20henchmen%20used%20burner%20phones%2C%20encrypting%20their%20messages%20and%20emails.%20With%20so%20many%20artists%20coming%20and%20going%20on%20various%20projects%2C%20no%20one%20was%20the%20wiser%20as%20contraband-filled%20road%20cases%20shipped%20through%20Interscope%20Records%2C%20the%20label%20co-founded%20by%20music%20legend%20Jimmy%20Iovine.%20(Interscope%20denied%20any%20involvement%20in%20the%20drug%20enterprise.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20now%2C%20Mario%20had%20determinedly%20stayed%20out%20of%20Jimmy's%20underworld.%20He%20was%20remaking%20his%20life%20in%20LA%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20streets%20he%20had%20left%20behind.%20But%20there%20was%20one%20problem%20for%20Mario.%20%26quot%3BHe'll%20do%20whatever%20for%20his%20family%20and%20for%20his%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20his%20friend%20DJ%20Skee.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20extremely%20loyal%20to%20a%20fault.%26quot%3B%20So%20when%20Jimmy%20asked%20him%20for%20help%2C%20Mario%20couldn't%20say%20no.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20I%20got%20back%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20He%20made%20sure%20the%20drug%20money%20%26quot%3Bgot%20to%20where%20it's%20supposed%20to%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20brotherly%20favor%20put%20Mario%20in%20the%20crosshairs.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20he%20got%20a%20late-night%20call%20from%20a%20neighbor%2C%20the%20only%20other%20Black%20guy%20who%20lived%20in%20his%20ritzy%20Hollywood%20Hills%20development.%20The%20Feds%20had%20busted%20down%20the%20guy's%20door%20by%20mistake%2C%20looking%20for%20Mario.%20It%20was%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20Mario%20found%20himself%20in%20custody.%20And%20that%20meant%2C%20as%20he%20saw%20it%2C%20there%20was%20only%20one%20choice.%20He%20called%20up%20a%20loyal%20contact%20in%20the%20Henchmen%20network.%20%26quot%3BThey%20busted%20down%20my%20man's%20door%20looking%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20told%20him.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20have%20in%20your%20trick%20bag%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20gonna%20need%2050%20grand%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guy%20replied.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20go%20to%20Mexico%20and%20set%20it%20up%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EHe%20called%20his%20daughter%20to%20say%20goodbye.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20trouble%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20her.%20%26quot%3BI%20gotta%20get%20outta%20here.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guy%20said%20he%20would%20spread%20the%20money%20through%20a%20decentralized%20network%20of%20people%20who%20could%20smuggle%20Mario%20across%20the%20border.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20Mario%20couldn't%20go%20home.%20%26quot%3BThis%20place%20don't%20exist%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guy%20told%20him.%20Another%20handler%20picked%20him%20up%20and%20took%20him%20to%20a%20hotel%2C%20the%20first%20of%20three%20he'd%20be%20staying%20at%20over%20the%20next%20few%20days%20until%20they%20could%20get%20him%20to%20Mexico.%20From%20this%20moment%20forward%2C%20Mario%20was%20on%20the%20run%20%E2%80%94%20just%20as%20Jimmy%20had%20been%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20his%20phony%20identity%2C%20Mario%20slipped%20an%20envelope%20containing%20%245%2C000%20in%20cash%20to%20a%20contact%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Motor%20Vehicles.%20When%20his%20new%20ID%20was%20ready%2C%20the%20contact%20called%20him%20from%20a%20burner%20phone%20and%20told%20him%20what%20day%20to%20come%20by%20the%20DMV.%20When%20Mario%20arrived%2C%20he%20snaked%20around%20in%20line%20until%20the%20contact%20lit%20his%20red%20light%2C%20signaling%20him%20to%20come%20over.%20That's%20when%20Mario%20was%20handed%20an%20authentic%20California%20driver's%20license%20with%20his%20new%20identity%3A%20Tommy%20Davis.%20When%20I%20ask%20how%20he%20felt%20about%20the%20random%20name%20he%20was%20given%2C%20Mario%20chuckles.%20%26quot%3BDidn't%20make%20no%20difference%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20he%20was%20over%20the%20border%2C%20however%2C%20Mario%20would%20lose%20what%20mattered%20most%20to%20him%3A%20his%20family.%20It%20would%20be%20too%20risky%20to%20speak%20with%20them%20again.%20He%20called%20his%20eldest%20daughter%20back%20in%20New%20Jersey%20to%20say%20goodbye.%20She%20was%20in%20her%2030s%2C%20with%20a%20family%20of%20her%20own.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20trouble%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20her.%20%26quot%3BI%20gotta%20get%20outta%20here.%26quot%3B%20All%20he%20could%20do%20was%20listen%20to%20her%20cry%20as%20he%20explained%20that%20he%20didn't%20know%20when%20he'd%20be%20back.%20Then%20he%20told%20his%20two%20little%20kids%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20%26quot%3BDaddy's%20sorry%2C%20but%20he%20has%20to%20go%20take%20care%20of%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20like%20when%20I%20go%20out%20and%20travel%20for%20business.%20So%20you're%20not%20gonna%20see%20me%20for%20a%20little%20while.%26quot%3B%20He%20ate%20his%20last%20meal%20at%20Crustacean%20in%20Beverly%20Hills%2C%20ordering%20his%20favorites%3A%20crabs%2C%20garlic%20noodles%2C%20and%20the%20mango%20lobster%20appetizer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20morning%2C%20he%20got%20instructions%20to%20go%20to%20a%20nearby%20supermarket%2C%20where%20a%20black%20Suburban%20would%20be%20waiting%20to%20pick%20him%20up.%20He%20took%20one%20duffel%20bag%20of%20clothes%20and%20another%20filled%20with%20%2450%2C000%20in%20cash%20%E2%80%94%20enough%2C%20he%20hoped%2C%20to%20last%20him%20wherever%20he%20was%20going%20in%20Mexico.%20During%20the%20drive%20south%2C%20Mario%20called%20Jimmy%20on%20his%20burner%20phone.%20They%20had%20to%20be%20vague%2C%20since%20the%20Feds%20could%20be%20listening.%20%26quot%3BYo%2C%20dude%2C%26quot%3B%20Mario%20said.%20%26quot%3BMan%2C%20you%20should%20really%20make%20this%20move%20with%20me%2C%20Jimmy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20go%20with%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20replied.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20two%20of%20us%20together%20is%20gonna%20bring%20too%20much%20heat.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20too%20had%20an%20escape%20plan.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20working%20on%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBased%20what%20I'm%20working%20on%2C%20maybe%20someday%20I'll%20be%20able%20to%20come%20and%20see%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario's%20driver%20zipped%20them%20through%20the%20border%20patrol%20at%20San%20Ysidro%20without%20Mario%20needing%20to%20show%20his%20new%20ID%2C%20and%20then%20handed%20him%20off%20in%20Tijuana%20to%20his%20next%20liaison%2C%20who%20checked%20him%20in%20to%20a%20hotel.%20%26quot%3BBe%20at%20the%20airport%20at%208%20a.m.%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20man%20told%20him.%20Once%20there%2C%20Mario%20went%20to%20the%20specified%20counter%20where%20the%20attendant%2C%20who%20was%20on%20the%20take%2C%20issued%20him%20a%20ticket%20under%20his%20Tommy%20Davis%20alias.%20His%20destination%3A%20Mexico%20City.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario's%20mouth%20went%20dry.%20He%20didn't%20speak%20Spanish%2C%20didn't%20know%20a%20soul%20in%20Mexico%2C%20and%20had%20no%20clue%20where%20he%20would%20be%20sent.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20thirsty%20cuz%20I%20was%20nervous%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20'What%20am%20I%20walking%20into%3F'%20'Cause%20I%20don't%20know%20nothing.%20But%20I%20trusted%20my%20man%2C%20you%20know%2C%20I%20trust%20him%20with%20my%20life.%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20choice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225023%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mexican%20town%20of%20Cuernavaca%2C%20shot%20from%20a%20distance%20with%20vegetation%20surrounding%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c28e99cf07780019653f56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223767%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELiving%20on%20the%20run%20in%20Cuernavaca%2C%20Mario%20changed%20apartments%20every%20six%20months.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20never%20attached%20to%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3Cp%3EGummyBone%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20arriving%20in%20Mexico%20City%2C%20Mario%20called%20a%20number%20he'd%20been%20given.%20An%20athletic%20Colombian%20guy%20pulled%20up%20outside%20with%20his%20Mexican%20fianc%C3%A9e%20in%20the%20passenger%20seat.%20%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20Mexico%20City%2C%20man%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Mario%20with%20a%20smile.%20The%20Colombian%20had%20been%20on%20the%20run%20from%20trouble%20in%20San%20Diego%20for%2015%20years.%20Mario%20didn't%20ask%20why%2C%20and%20the%20guy%20didn't%20inquire%20about%20Mario's%20predicament.%20They%20drove%2050%20miles%20south%20until%20they%20came%20to%20the%20hillside%20town%20of%20Cuernavaca%20and%20the%20apartment%20Mario%20would%20share%20with%20the%20couple.%20From%20there%2C%20he%20was%20on%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20adjusted%20to%20his%20strange%20new%20life%20in%20Mexico%2C%20Mario%20went%20to%20an%20internet%20caf%C3%A9%20each%20day%2C%20checking%20the%20news%20from%20back%20home.%20On%20June%2021%2C%202011%2C%20scanning%20the%20New%20York%20Post%2C%20he%20saw%20a%20headline%3A%20%26quot%3BFugitive%20hip%20hop%20talent%20agent%20Rosemond%20charged%20with%20running%20drug%20ring.%26quot%3B%20The%20story%20was%20accompanied%20by%20a%20photo%20of%20Jimmy%20in%20handcuffs%2C%20escorted%20by%20two%20agents%20from%20the%20Drug%20Enforcement%20Administration.%20They%20had%20busted%20him%20on%20his%20way%20out%20of%20the%20W%20Hotel%20in%20Manhattan.%20The%20complaint%2C%20which%20mapped%20Jimmy's%20vast%20trafficking%20network%2C%20revealed%20that%20he'd%20been%20brought%20down%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20two%20DEA%20informants%20in%20his%20organization.%20One%20was%20his%20longtime%20friend%20Tef%20Stewart.%20The%20other%20was%20his%20top%20lieutenant%2C%20Khalil%20Abdullah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20got%20worse.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20Jimmy%20was%20indicted%20on%20an%20even%20more%20serious%20charge%3A%20murder%20for%20hire.%20The%20Feds%20accused%20him%20of%20recruiting%20a%20crew%20of%20hitmen%20to%20kill%20Fletcher%20in%20return%20for%20%2430%2C000%20of