couldn't%20let%20them%20know%20anything%20about%20his%20location%20or%20situation.%20His%20%2450%2C000%20was%20dwindling%2C%20and%20he%20didn't%20have%20a%20way%20to%20drum%20up%20more%20money.%20So%20he%20worked%20out%20twice%20a%20day%2C%20and%20went%20to%20church%20to%20pray%2C%20and%20hoped%20for%20something%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20one%20day%2C%20after%20eight%20years%20on%20the%20run%2C%20something%20did.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario%2C%20normally%20so%20careful%20and%20meticulous%2C%20acknowledges%20he%20had%20gotten%20sloppy.%20Tired%20of%20his%20life%20as%20Tommy%20Davis%2C%20alone%20in%20Cuernavaca%2C%20he%20had%20started%20calling%20home%20more%20often%2C%20and%20took%20fewer%20precautions%20to%20cover%20his%20tracks.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20lazy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20as%20he%20was%20in%20the%20courtyard%20doing%20his%20laundry%2C%20he%20thought%20the%20men%20he%20spotted%20scaling%20the%20fence%20were%20Mexican%20Federales.%20He%20tried%20to%20play%20it%20cool%20when%20they%20confronted%20him%2C%20but%20they%20ordered%20him%20to%20lie%20face%20down%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20pointed%20their%20weapons%20at%20him%2C%20freckling%20him%20with%20red%20laser%20dots.%20%3Cem%3EOh%2C%20my%20God%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehe%20thought.%20%3Cem%3EI'm%20gonna%20die%20today.%20They're%20gonna%20kill%20me.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIt%20was%20only%20after%20a%20long%2C%20silent%20ride%20in%20the%20back%20of%20a%20pickup%20truck%20when%20his%20hood%20was%20removed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20found%20himself%20staring%20into%20the%20eyes%20of%20a%20US%20Marshal%20at%20the%20Mexico%20City%20airport.%20He%20still%20doesn't%20know%20who%20ratted%20him%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMario%20was%20headed%20back%20to%20New%20York%20to%20face%20the%20drug-trafficking%20charges%20he'd%20evaded%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade.%20But%20he%20felt%20as%20though%20his%20arrest%20had%20actually%20released%20him%20from%20the%20prison%20of%20his%20assumed%20identity.%20Tommy%20Davis%20was%20no%20more.%20All%20that%20remained%20was%20Mario%20Rosemond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20relief%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BCuz%20no%20matter%20what%20anyone%20say%2C%20a%20double%20life%20is%20the%20most%20difficult%20thing%20to%20keep.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20arrest%2C%20Mario%20spent%20a%20year%20in%20federal%20prison%20in%20New%20York%20before%20he%20was%20released%20to%20live%20with%20his%20daughter's%20family%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20where%20he's%20now%20awaiting%20sentencing.%20He%20will%20plead%20guilty%20to%20one%20count%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20distribute%20cocaine%2C%20which%20could%20send%20him%20away%20for%20five%20years%20to%20life.%20But%20Mario%2C%20who%20spends%20his%20days%20taking%20care%20of%20his%20grandson%2C%20isn't%20running%20anymore.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20peace%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me%20outside%20his%20daughter's%20home.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20ready%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20bad%20deeds%20and%20then%20go%20on%20with%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20he's%20sharing%20his%20story%20with%20me%2C%20he%20says%2C%20is%20to%20discourage%20others%20from%20following%20his%20path.%20%26quot%3BDealing%20with%20any%20kind%20of%20illegalities%2C%20it%20ain't%20worth%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI've%20had%20all%20the%20money%20that%20I%20could%20possibly%20have%2C%20right%3F%20No%20matter%20how%20smart%20you%20think%20you%20are%2C%20the%20government%20has%20enough%20people%20on%20their%20payroll%20to%20outsmart%20you.%20It%20can%20go%20for%20a%20month%20or%20it%20can%20go%20for%20years%2C%20like%20for%20me.%20But%20sooner%20or%20later%20it%20catches%20up%20to%20you.%20So%20I%20would%20like%20to%20tell%20the%20younger%20generation%20coming%20up%20to%20try%20to%20do%20it%20a%20different%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20headshot%20of%20Jim%20Brown%2C%20Donald%2