20many%20borrowers%20in%20limbo%2C%20with%20some%20having%20to%20pay%20the%20debt%20of%20their%20ex-spouse.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETheresa%2C%2051%2C%20divorced%20her%20then-husband%20in%202016.%20Seven%20years%20later%2C%20she's%20still%20paying%20off%20his%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Theresa%20%E2%80%94%20who%20requested%20her%20last%20name%20be%20withheld%20for%20privacy%20%E2%80%94%20graduated%20from%20college%20in%20the%2090s%2C%20she%C2%A0and%20her%20ex-husband%20decided%20that%20combining%20their%20student%20debt%20balances%20would%20be%20the%20best%20option%20for%20them%20financially%20since%20it%20would%20allow%20them%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20debt%20together%20with%20a%20single%20interest%20rate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20combine%20their%20balances%20in%202003%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarried-couples-blocked-from-student-loan-forgiveness-after-combining-balances-2022-5%5C%22%3Etheir%20loans%20became%20part%20of%20the%20spousal%20joint%20consolidation%20loan%20program%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20Congress%20shuttered%20the%20program%20in%202006%2C%20meaning%20borrowers%20who%20combined%20their%20debt%20before%20then%20had%20no%20way%20to%20separate%20their%20balances%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20divorce%2C%20domestic%20violence%2C%20or%20other%20financial%20reasons.%20That's%20why%20Sen.%20Mark%20Warner%20and%20Rep.%20David%20Price%20introduced%20the%20Joint%20Consolidation%20Loan%20Separation%20Act%20of%202021%20%E2%80%94%20and%20last%20year%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspousal-student-loan-borrowers-can-separate-balances-debt-relief-forgiveness-2022-9%5C%22%3Esigned%20the%20legislation%20into%20law%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20feature%20of%20the%20new%20law%20is%20that%20one%20spouse%20can%20apply%20for%20relief%20even%20if%20the%20other%20is%20being%20uncooperative.%20%26quot%3BThe%20critical%20thing%20is%20that%20this%20bill%20also%20allows%20a%20disadvantaged%20spouse%20to%20apply%2C%26quot%3B%20Price%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspousal-student-loan-borrowers-can-separate-balances-debt-relief-forgiveness-2022-9%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIf%20their%20spouse%20is%20unresponsive%2C%20abusive%2C%20or%20economically%20irresponsible%2C%20the%20spouse%20can%20apply%20for%20the%20severance%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20where%20his%20or%20her%20portion%20of%20it%20is%20assigned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20been%20nearly%20a%20year%20since%20the%20law%20was%20passed%2C%20and%20the%20Education%20Department%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsapartners.ed.gov%2Fknowledge-center%2Flibrary%2Felectronic-announcements%2F2023-07-19%2Fjoint-consolidation-loan-separation-act-forbearance-guidance%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR1qcC1pbJJUuBtobCGUjWX0TItN98ggazvCTtiLBg8GPnt4Gy9uFD1lo5A_aem_AaeMMfaldLDGbfiClwvsVKNlacctDdX-sluc9XohQZ8dI4FsByKTr2BWacvUNsdSskE%26mibextid%3DZxz2cZ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estated%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%26quot%3Bprocess%20will%20not%20be%20fully%20implemented%20until%20late%202024%20at%20the%20earliest.%26quot%3B%20The%20guidance%20did%20not%20include%20a%20reasoning%20for%20this%20timeline.%C2%A0%20Borrowers%20do%20have%20the%20option%20to%20request%20their%20servicer%20place%20their%20loans%20in%20forbearance%20until%20then%2C%20the%20department%20wrote%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsapartners.ed.gov%2Fknowledge-center%2Flibrary%2Felectronic-announcements%2F2023-07-19%2Fjoint-consolidation-loan-separation-act-forbearance-guidance%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR1qcC1pbJJUuBtobCGUjWX0TItN98ggazvCTtiLBg8GPnt4Gy9uFD1lo5A_aem_AaeMMfaldLDGbfiClwvsVKNlacctDdX-sluc9XohQZ8dI4FsByKTr2BWacvUNsdSskE%26mibextid%3DZxz2cZ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguidance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20wouldn't%20owe%20payments%2C%20and%20if%20approved%20for%20administrative%20forbearance%2C%20their%20interest%20rates%20would%20be%20set%20to%20zero.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20left%20Theresa%20%E2%80%94%20and%20other%20borrowers%20with%20spousal%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20state%20of%20limbo%20because%20her%20loans%20are%20privately-held%2C%20meaning%20they%20did%20not%20qualify%20for%20the%20federal%20student-loan%20payment%20pause%2C%20and%20she's%20encountered%20issues%20placing%20her%20loans%20on%20administrative%20forbearance.%20Though%20she%20started%20with%20a%20balance%20of%20%2417%2C000%20before%20consolidation%2C%20her%20total%20balance%20now%20stands%20at%20just%20over%20%2430%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20which%20she%20said%20belonged%20to%20her%20ex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20devastating%2C%26quot%3B%20Theresa%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20it%20feels%20almost%20like%20my%20divorce%20hasn't%20been%20finalized.%20When%20you%20go%20through%20the%20divorce%20process%2C%20the%20first%20step%20is%20a%20legal%20separation%20which%20protects%20you%20financially%20from%20your%20soon-to-be%20ex-spouse.%20So%20you'd%20have%20some%20protection%20if%20they%20make%20some%20poor%20financial%20decisions.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20it's%20like%20the%20goalpost%20for%20divorce%20just%20keeps%20moving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'They're%20just%20not%20regular%20student%20loans'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-do-separate-spousal-student-loan-debt-balance-new-guidance-2023-5%5C%22%3Ereleased%20guidance%20for%20borrowers%20with%20spousal%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20process%20for%20separation%20after%20the%20bill%20to%20do%20so%20was%20signed%20into%20law.%20Per%20the%20guidance%2C%20borrowers%20will%20either%20be%20able%20to%20submit%20a%20joint%20application%20with%20their%20spouse%20or%20do%20so%20individually%2C%20but%20since%20it's%20not%20yet%20available%2C%20borrowers%20should%20contact%20the%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20Ombudsman%20Group%20to%20indicate%20they%20intend%20to%20apply%20to%20separate%20their%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowers%20with%20federal%20direct%20loans%20can%20contact%20their%20servicers%20to%20request%20to%20be%20placed%20in%20forbearance%20until%20the%20process%20is%20implemented%2C%20and%20the%20department%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudentaid.gov%2Fannouncements-events%2Fjoint-consolidation-loans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20lenders%20are%20%26quot%3Bencouraged%20to%20grant%20discretionary%20forbearances%26quot%3B%20to%20those%20with%20privately-held%20loans%20in%20the%20Federal%20Family%20Education%20Loan%20(FFEL)%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheresa%20said%20her%20student-loan%20servicer%20has%20yet%20to%20grant%20her%20administrative%20forbearance%2C%20and%20when%20she%20attempted%20to%20seek%20a%20hardship%20forbearance%2C%20she%20was%20told%20she%20needed%20her%20ex-husband's%20permission%20because%20she%20is%20not%20the%20primary%20borrower%20on%20the%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20access.%20I%20can't%20see%20the%20account%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20barely%20get%20through%20when%20I%20call%20because%20everything%20is%20under%20his%20name.%20I%20don't%20exist%20in%20their%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrigid%2C%20a%2055-year-old%20borrower%20with%20spousal%20loans%2C%20told%20Insider%20she's%20experienced%20a%20similar%20dilemma.%20After%20six%20months%20of%20back-and-forth%20with%20her%20servicer%20to%20request%20administrative%20forbearance%2C%20she%20said%20she%20finally%20received%20it%20this%20past%20week%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20said%20she's%20frustrated%20that%20interest%20continued%20to%20accumulate%20during%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20husband%20was%20also%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer%20about%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20and%20she%20attempted%20to%20get%20a%20deferment%20on%20her%20loans%20due%20to%20his%20medical%20treatment.%20However%2C%20because%20of%20the%20strict%20nature%20of%20spousal%20loans%2C%20she%20would%20also%20have%20to%20meet%20the%20hardship%20requirements%20by%2C%20for%20example%2C%20also%20having%20cancer%20in%20order%20to%20receive%20the%20deferment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20extraordinary%2C%20and%20that%20is%20the%20perfect%20illustration%20of%20what%20a%20mess%20these%20loans%20are.%20They're%20just%20not%20regular%20student%20loans%2C%26quot%3B%20Brigid%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20horrible.%20They%20really%20are.%20That%20was%20the%20worst%20kick%20in%20the%20pants%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'It's%20just%20emotionally%20exhausting'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20borrowers%20with%20joint%20loans%20who%20separated%20from%20their%20spouse%2C%20the%20inability%20to%20make%20decisions%20about%20repayment%20individually%20can%20take%20a%20toll%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20dealing%20with%20the%20bureaucracy%20of%20student-loan%20servicers.%20Theresa%20said%20that%20at%20one%20point%2C%20her%20servicer%20mixed%20up%20her%20address%20and%20the%20address%20of%20her%20ex-husband%2C%20but%20when%20she%20called%20to%20have%20that%20fixed%2C%20she%20was%20told%20she%20could%20not%20make%20any%20changes%20without%20her%20ex's%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20at%20least%20an%20hour%20wait%20on%20hold.%20And%20then%20when%20I%20get%20to%20the%20phone%20tree%2C%20it'll%20take%20me%20probably%20three%20or%20four%20times%20just%20to%20get%20to%20a%20person%20because%20when%20I%20enter%20my%20identifying%20information%20and%20birth%20date%2C%20they%20don't%20recognize%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Theresa%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20just%20emotionally%20exhausting%20to%20be%20reminded%20each%20time%20that%20you%20don't%20really%20exist%20in%20the%20system%2C%20but%20they'll%20gladly%20take%20your%20payment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%2C%2043%2C%20combined%20her%20balance%20with%20her%20husband%20in%202005%20to%20lock%20in%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20told%20Insider%20she%20wants%20to%20separate%20their%20balance%20so%20it%20no%20longer%20gets%20reported%20twice%20on%20their%20credit%20reports.%20Since%20both%20her%20and%20her%20husband%20are%20liable%20for%20the%20debt%2C%20the%20full%20amount%20of%20their%20balance%20shows%20up%20on%20each%20of%20their%20credit%20reports.%20But%20she's%20been%20unable%20to%20receive%20administrative%20forbearance%2C%20and%20she's%20frustrated%20borrowers%20with%20spousal%20loans%20are%20blocked%20from%20opportunities%20federal%20borrowers%20are%20receiving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20the%20whole%20concept%20of%20treating%20married%20people%20differently%20for%20this%20type%20of%20loan%20has%20been%20a%20nightmare%20of%20unequal%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20Elizabeth%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20pay%20this%20debt%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other.%20What%20I'm%20angry%20about%20is%20that%20I%20paid%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest%20while%20everybody%20else's%20interest%20was%20frozen%20in%20time%20through%20no%20choices%20of%20my%20own.%20And%20I%20would%20have%20paid%20my%20debt%20down%20faster%20and%20I%20might%20even%20be%20debt-free%20if%20I%20had%20been%20treated%20the%20same%20as%20every%20other%20person.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20borrowers%20who%20are%20hoping%20to%20separate%20their%20balances%20with%20a%20spouse%20can%20do%20right%20now%20is%20wait%20for%20the%20Education%20Department%20to%20implement%20the%20law%20%E2%80%94%20and%20continue%20to%20contact%20their%20servicers%20for%20administrative%20forbearance.%20Still%2C%20as%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-payments-resume-confusion-borrowers-debt-relief-biden-2023-8%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20servicers%20are%20already%20swamped%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-payment-pause-is-over-interest-resuming-borrower-balances-2023-8%5C%22%3Efederal%20student-loan%20system%20starting%20back%20up%20again%20in%20October%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20getting%20help%20from%20customer%20service%20is%20no%20easy%20feat%2C%20leaving%20many%20borrowers%20without%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20single%20parent%2C%20and%20life%20is%20uncertain%20and%20I%20need%20to%20do%20what%20I%20need%20to%20do%20to%20protect%20myself%20and%20my%20daughter%2C%26quot%3B%20Theresa%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%2C%20as%20much%20as%20it%20kills%20me%20every%20month%2C%20I%20make%20that%20payment%20because%20I%20don't%20really%20have%20any%20other%20good%20options%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-spousal-loans-be-separated-student-debt-relief-forgiveness-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694944801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60ba6ba393c6fa00195e543d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-spousal-loans-be-separated-student-debt-relief-forgiveness-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nearly%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20a%20law%20was%20passed%20to%20allow%20student-loan%20borrowers%20to%20separate%20their%20balances%20from%20their%20spouse's.%20They're%20still%20waiting%20for%20relief.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-spousal-loans-be-separated-student-debt-relief-forgiveness-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20former%20Californians%20share%20why%20they%20decided%20to%20chase%20the%20American%20dream%20in%20Texas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%