icier.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20living%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20having%20on%20his%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20knew%20that%20when%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20eventually%20expanded%20our%20family%2C%20we%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20San%20Francisco%20or%20the%20Bay%20Area%20in%20general%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20we%20both%20earn%20good%20salaries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20couple%20packed%20up%20their%20bags%20and%20headed%20to%20Texas.%C2%A0Cheng%20isn't%20the%20only%20Californian%20chasing%20the%20American%20dream%20in%20Texas.%20The%20path%20from%20California%20to%20Texas%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20popular%20interstate%20relocation%20route%20in%20the%20US.%20In%202021%2C%20almost%20108%2C000%20people%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.storagecafe.com%2Fblog%2Fcalifornia-to-texas-moving%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emigrated%20from%20California%20to%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20the%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Fgeographic-mobility%2Fstate-to-state-migration.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20median%20home%20sale%20price%20in%20Texas%20was%20%24356%2C200%20compared%20to%20%24783%2C300%20in%20California%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin.%20Texas'%20cost%20of%20living%20is%208%25%20below%20the%20national%20average%2C%20while%20California's%20is%2042%25%20higher%2C%20according%20to%20RentCafe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Texas%20flag%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6503560b956dba001acdad6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EP%20A%20Thompson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20affordability%20is%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20many%20Californians%20relocating%20to%20Texas%2C%20there%20are%20other%20factors%20drawing%20them%20to%20the%20state.%20Three%20Californians%20who%20have%20moved%20to%20Texas%20in%20recent%20years%20told%20Insider%20about%20the%20positives%20of%20the%20move%20and%20the%20negatives%20they%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Chengs%20found%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPengyu%20Cheng's%20desire%20to%20leave%20California%20peaked%20during%202020.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20were%20living%20in%20a%20two-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20apartment%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20burdened%20with%20a%20%243%2C100%20monthly%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20COVID-19%20shut%20down%20the%20city%2C%20Cheng%20felt%20as%20if%20he%20and%20his%20wife's%20hard-earned%20money%20was%20being%20squandered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20couldn't%20go%20anywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20paying%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20live%20in%20a%20city%20we%20weren't%20enjoying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chengs%20knew%20it%20was%20time%20to%20move.%20They%20wanted%20to%20relocate%20to%20an%20affordable%20city%20with%20amenities%20like%20parks%2C%20hiking%20trails%2C%20and%20easy%20access%20to%20grocery%20stores%20and%20restaurants.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22938%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pengyu%20Cheng%20and%20his%20family.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6503554d2a72d60019d53ca2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22705%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECheng%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20son.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Pengyu%20Cheng.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20chose%20Austin.%20The%20couple%20had%20visited%20the%20city%20a%20few%20times%2C%20and%20it%20came%20highly%20recommended%20by%20their%20friends.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20they%20went%20from%20being%20squeezed%20inside%20a%20small%20apartment%20in%20San%20Francisco%20to%20living%20in%20a%20five-bedroom%2C%20three-and-a-half%20bathroom%20home%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Austin%20that%20they%20purchased%20for%20%24825%2C000.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20really%20consider%20buying%20a%20home%20in%20San%20Francisco%20because%20every%20time%20we%20looked%20at%20Redfin%20or%20read%20an%20article%20about%20median%20housing%20prices%2C%20it%20was%20the%20same%20story%3A%20The%20real%20estate%20market%20was%20just%20getting%20more%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20perk%20of%20becoming%20homeowners%2C%20the%20Chengs%20have%20found%20a%20more%20balanced%20and%20community-oriented%20lifestyle%20in%20Austin.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20most%20of%20the%20conversations%20you%20hear%20are%20related%20to%20entrepreneurship%20or%20moving%20up%20in%20a%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20living%20in%20Austin%2C%20it%20has%20been%20refreshing%20to%20hear%20stories%20about%20weekend%20soccer%20practice%20for%20the%20kids%20or%20community%20gatherings%20and%20concerts.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJackie%20Burse%20feels%20more%20at%20ease%20expressing%20her%20opinions%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20native%20Californian%20Jackie%20Burse%2C%2058%2C%20left%20Orange%20County%20for%20San%20Antonio%2C%20Texas.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20Burse%20was%20renting%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20for%20about%20%241%2C900%20a%20month.%20In%20San%20Antonio%2C%20she%20now%20rents%20a%20three-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20house%20for%20%241%2C600%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20divorced%20mother%20of%20two%20told%20Insider%20that%20affordability%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20her%20decision%2C%20as%20well%20the%20state's%20political%20atmosphere.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221070%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jackie%20Burse%20grabbing%20a%20drin