%20Helplines%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComprehensive%20primary%20care%2C%20espoused%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fteams%2Fsocial-determinants-of-health%2Fdeclaration-of-alma-ata%5C%22%3EAlma%20Ata%20declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%201978%2C%20was%20cast%20aside%20for%20selective%20primary%20care%20and%20vertical%20programmes%20that%20were%20mainly%20donor-driven.%20Vertical%20programmes%20typically%20focus%20on%20a%20specific%20condition%20or%20group%20of%20health%20problems%20and%20often%20have%20only%20short%20or%20medium-term%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3EUniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20not%20considered%20an%20essential%20function%20of%20national%20health%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SDG%20agenda%20overcomes%20these%20distortions%20by%20adopting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Four-work%2Flife-course%5C%22%3Ea%20life-course%20approach%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20gives%20priority%20to%20all%20major%20problems%20undermining%20health%20and%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESDG-3%20also%20identified%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3Euniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20the%20broad%20platform%20that%20could%20deliver%20health%20services%20while%20offering%20financial%20protection%20against%20inordinate%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fsocial-issues-migration-health%2Fhealth-at-a-glance-2009%2Fburden-of-out-of-pocket-health-expenditure_health_glance-2009-62-en%23page1%5C%22%3Eout-of-pocket%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20debilitating%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fsocial-issues-migration-health%2Fhealth-at-a-glance-2009%2Fburden-of-out-of-pocket-health-expenditure_health_glance-2009-62-en%23page1%5C%22%3Ecatastrophic%20health%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20expenditures%20were%20imposed%20by%20severe%20and%20often%20acute%20health%20conditions%20that%20called%20for%20hospital%20care%20and%20costly%20interventions.%20Their%20chronic%20burdens%20can%20push%20people%20%E2%80%94%20or%20sink%20them%20deeper%20%E2%80%94%20into%20debt-ridden%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3EUniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20adequately%20financed%20and%20efficiently%20delivered%2C%20offers%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3Emuch-needed%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0through%20high%20levels%20of%20population%20coverage%2C%20service%20coverage%20and%20cost%20coverage.%20Affirmation%20of%20comprehensive%20primary%20care%20as%20the%20lead%20vehicle%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3Euniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0convoy%20came%20as%20a%20clarion%20call%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2Freport-of-the-global-conference-on-primary-health-care-from-alma-ata-towards-universal-health-coverage-and-the-sustainable-development-goals%5C%22%3EAstana%20Declaration%20of%202018%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202015%20and%202019%2C%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20started%20working%20towards%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals.%20However%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789290209881%5C%22%3Eprogress%20was%20slow%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20many%20countries%20due%20to%20under-resourced%20health%20systems%2C%20shortages%20of%20skilled%20health%20workers%20and%20a%20hangover%20of%20restrictive%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(97)90079-9%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Evertical%20programmes%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0still%20attuned%20to%20preset%20donor%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20there%20have%20been%20some%20successes%20too.%20India%20saw%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmaternal-mortality-ratio-drops-to-97-in-2018-2020-from-130-in-2014-2016-3564201%5C%22%3Ea%20sharp%20decline%20in%20maternal%20mortality%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(from%20407%20maternal%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20live%20births%20in%202000%20to%2097%20during%202018-20).%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdhsprogram.com%2Fpubs%2Fpdf%2FFR375%2FFR375.pdf%5C%22%3EInfant%20mortality%20rates%20halved%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%2053.6%20deaths%20per%201%2C000%20live%20births%20in%202006%20to%2026.6%20in%202023.%20Under-five%20mortality%20fell%20too.%20These%20declines%20became%20sharper%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3026119%2F%5C%22%3ENational%20Rural%20Health%20Mission%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20health%20system%20efforts%20on%20newly%20adopted%20priorities%2C%20like%20non-communicable%20diseases%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20were%20still%20struggling%20to%20gather%20momentum.%20The%20burden%20of%20non-communicable%20diseases%20continued%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(17)32804-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Espiral%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20initially%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20but%20later%20engulfing%20rural%20populations%20as%20well.%20Those%20trends%20have%20continued%20over%20recent%20years%20in%20India%20and%20other%20South%20Asian%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emergence%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20continued%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789290209881%5C%22%3Ehamper%20progress%20towards%20SDG-3%20targets%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%20Health%20system%20resources%20were%20focused%20mostly%20on%20combating%20and%20containing%20the%20virus%20and%20saving%20lives.%20Other%20health%20services%20were%20sidelined%20or%20stalled%20and%20critical%20health%20efforts%20related%20to%20SDGs%20were%20deprioritised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fnitrogen-oxides-emissions-increasing-in-south-asia-says-soga-report%5C%22%3EWith%20Delhi%20Atop%20List%20of%20PM2.5%20Exposed%20Cities%2C%20Nitrogen%20Oxide%20Emissions%20Also%20Rise%20in%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20issues%20are%20especially%20acute%20in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%20There%20are%2014%20countries%20in%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20region%20where%20maternal%20mortality%20rates%20are%20higher%20than%20the%20regional%20average%20and%20likely%20to%20fall%20short%20of%20the%20SDG%20target%20of%20fewer%20than%2070%20maternal%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20live%20births%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20United%20Nations%20Population%20Fund%20review%20of%202020%20found%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789240068759%5C%22%3Eeven%20higher%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0than%20previously%20recorded%20because%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20attention%20is%20still%20on%20pandemic%20prevention%2C%20preparedness%20and%20response%2C%20with%20microbial%20surveillance%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Fone-health%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3EOne%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20an%20approach%20that%20recognizes%20the%20health%20of%20people%20being%20closely%20connected%20to%20the%20health%20of%20animals%20and%20environments%20%E2%80%94%20emerging%20as%20major%20themes%20of%20ongoing%20global%20health%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevision%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789241580496%5C%22%3EInternational%20Health%20Regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Fquestions-and-answers%2Fitem%2Fpandemic-prevention--preparedness-and-response-accord%5C%22%3Enew%20pandemic%20accord%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0are%20on%20course%20for%20adoption%20in%202024%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fantimicrobial-resistance%5C%22%3EAntimicrobial%20resistance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20another%20looming%20major%20public%20health%20threat.%20It%20is%20now%20being%20packed%20into%20the%20pandemic%20preparedness%20agenda%2C%20as%20evident%20from%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.g20.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fgtwenty%2Fgtwenty_new%2Fdocument%2FG20_HMM_Outcome_Document_and_Chair_Summary.pdf%5C%22%3Eoutcome%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20G20%20Health%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20Meeting%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20also%20recognises%20the%20threats%20posed%20to%20health%20by%20climate%20change%20and%20calls%20for%20climate-resilient%20and%20climate-smart%20health%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20seven%20years%20left%20to%20meet%20the%20SDG%20targets%2C%20the%20world%20must%20focus%20on%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3Eprimary%20care-led%20universal%20health%20coverage%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Emulti-sectoral%20actions%20across%20other%20SDGs%20to%20steer%20policies%20and%20programmes%20that%20will%20enable%20and%20not%20erode%20overall%20health%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eactive%20engagement%20of%20communities%20in%20all%20stages%20of%20health%20policies%20and%20programmes%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eincreasing%20global%20access%20to%20technologies%20that%20can%20protect%2C%20preserve%20and%20restore%20health%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20vaccines%2C%20diagnostics%20and%20drugs%20%E2%80%94%20without%20being%20hampered%20by%20profit-hungry%2C%20patent-restrictive%20practices%3B%20and%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eresearch%20and%20innovation%20that%20can%20identify%20and%20evaluate%20new%20methods%20to%20improve%20health%20system%20performance%2C%20such%20as%20digital%20technologies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20call%20for%20increased%20national%20and%20global%20financing%20for%20health%20systems%20and%20health-related%20multi-sectoral%20actions.%20It%20is%20futile%20to%20think%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments1.worldbank.org%2Fcurated%2Fen%2F979591495652724770%2Fpdf%2F115271-REVISED-FINAL-IWG-Report-3-5-18.pdf%5C%22%3Efinancing%20for%20health%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20is%20defined%20only%20in%20terms%20of%20acute%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20population%20health%20is%20the%20best%20overall%20indicator%20of%20success%20across%20all%20SDGs%2C%20global%20policymakers%20must%20give%20more%20funding%20to%20the%20health%20sector%20and%20health-relevant%20programmes%20in%20other%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImproved%20governance%20measures%20need%20to%20also%20ensure%20efficiency%20gains%20for%20money%20spent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpansion%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.who.int%2Firis%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10665%2F250368%2F9789241511131-eng.pdf%5C%22%3Ehealth%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0must%20also%20be%20a%20priority.%20A%20recent%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F35760437%2F%5C%22%3Eestimate%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0indicates%20that%20a%2015%20million%20shortage%20in%20the%20global%20health%20workforce%20in%202020%20will%20reduce%20to%2010%20million%20by%202030%20but%20with%20much%20slower%20progress%20in%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20African%20and%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20great%20danger%20that%20high-income%20countries%20with%20ageing%20populations%20will%20increasingly%20recruit%20health%20workers%20from%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20weakening%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20health%20systems.%20High-income%20countries%20must%20co-invest%20with%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20to%20educate%20and%20train%20the%20health%20workers%20in%20those%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20health%20workforce%20expansion%20must%20involve%20all%20categories%20of%20health%20workers%2C%20the%20greatest%20attention%20must%20be%20paid%20to%20those%20needed%20in%20primary%20care%2C%20which%20is%20pivotal%20to%20achieve%20Goal%203%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20sufficient%20global%20evidence%20on%20the%20impactful%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fequityhealthj.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs12939-021-01615-y%5C%22%3Eequity-promoting%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4785041%2F%5C%22%3Ecommunity%20health%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20improving%20maternal%20and%20child%20health%2C%20non-communicable%20diseases%2C%20mental%20health%20and%20pandemic%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20scale%20up%20and%20skill%20up%20this%20transformational%20component%20of%20the%20health%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20only%20hope%20that%20the%20policymakers%2C%20international%20organisations%20and%20development%20partners%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fconferences%2FSDGSummit2023%5C%22%3Emeeting%20in%20September%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20review%20progress%20on%20the%20SDGs%20will%20take%20the%20necessary%20steps%20to%20make%20this%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cb%3EK.%20Srinath%20Reddy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20distinguished%20professor%20at%20the%20Public%20Health%20Foundation%20of%20India.%20He%20is%20the%20former%20president%20of%20the%20foundation%20and%20formerly%20headed%20the%20Department%20of%20Cardiology%20at%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS).%20Professor%20Reddy%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Leadership%20Council%20of%20the%20UN%20Sustainable%20Development%20Solutions%20Network%20(SDSN)%20and%20chairs%20the%20Thematic%20Group%20on%20Health%20for%20the%20SDSN.%20He%20is%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Global%20Panel%20on%20Agriculture%20and%20Food%20Systems%20for%20Nutrition.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20a%20special%20report%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98State%20of%20the%20SDGs%E2%80%99%2C%20produced%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unsdsn.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EUN%20Sustainable%20Development%20Solutions%20Network%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0(SDSN).%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694943051000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F26180632%2F2018_5img22_May_2018_PTI5_22_2018_000132B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-must-be-fast-tracked-for-2030%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20might%C2%A0no%20longer%20be%20a%20public%20health%20emergency%C2%A0but%20the%20world%20is%20still%20facing%20a%20crisis%20in%20health%2C%20and%20progress%20on%C2%A0Sustainable%20Development%20Goal%203%20is%20under%20threat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-must-be-fast-tracked-for-2030%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vikas%20Khanna's%20sweet%20post%20for%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694942846000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103731501%2Cimgsize-27084.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fvikas-khanna-sh