0%99s%20nephew%2C%20Khayal%20Azimabadi%2C%20was%20already%20disposed%20of%20in%201954.%20When%20Dr.%20Nawab%2C%20a%20renowned%20surgeon%20from%20Bihar%2C%20found%20the%20place%20unfit%20to%20reside%2C%20he%20also%20sold%20his%20house%20and%20settled%20in%20Darbhanga.%20With%20his%20departure%2C%20the%20last%20program%20of%20the%20Muharram%20mourning%20at%20Hajiganj%20also%20came%20to%20a%20permanent%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17124756%2FShad_Azimabad.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22200%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673372%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22217%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPoet%20Shad%20Azimabadi.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20this%20also%20ended%20the%20legacy%20which%20was%20established%20in%20the%20vicinity%20by%20Syed%20Mujtaba%20Hussain%2C%20Syed%20Mustafa%20Hussai%2C%20Syed%20Qudrat%20Hussain%2C%20Mir%20Enayat%20Hussain%20Imdad%2C%20Syed%20Taqi%20Mir%2C%20and%20Syed%20Ali%20Mir%2C%20and%20their%20illustrious%20ancestors.%20Those%20who%20preferred%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20homeland%20were%20later%20forced%20to%20settle%20in%20safer%20Muslim%20localities%20in%20different%20quarters%20of%20Patna%20such%20as%20Moghalpura%2C%20Alamganj%2C%20Pathar%20Ki%20Masjid%2C%20Sultanganj%2C%20Sabzibagh%2C%20Phulwari%20and%20Danapur%2C%20among%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20riots%20of%201946%20and%20the%20consequent%20division%20of%20the%20country%20disturbed%20several%20religious%20activities%20including%20the%20Muharram%20mourning%20in%20Patna.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20to%20suffer%20was%20the%20Imambara%20of%20Mohsin%20Sahab%20at%20Hajiganj%20which%20organised%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMajalis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20until%201946.%20Every%20year%2C%20on%208%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Muharram%2C%20the%20Islamic%20standards%20(Alam)%20from%20Chamru%20Dandiya%20(famous%20for%20an%20extant%20Imambara)%20were%20received%20here%20which%2C%20on%2010%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Muharram%2C%20were%20further%20transported%20to%20the%20Karbala%20Mir%20Farhat%20Hussain%20of%20Lal%20Imli%20(a%20Mohalla%20near%20Patna%20City%20Railway%20Station%20with%20barely%20any%20Muslim%20population)%20for%20the%20final%20rites.%20But%20the%20circumstances%20sharply%20changed%20after%201946%20and%20the%20descendants%20of%20Mohsin%20Sahab%20had%20to%20sell%20all%20their%20properties%20including%20the%20said%20Imambara%20in%201956.%20Similar%20misfortune%20befell%20on%20the%20Imambara%20of%20Kaiwan%20Shikoh%20also%20putting%20an%20end%20to%20the%20procession%20of%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Safar%20(Chehlum)%20which%20originated%20from%20the%20house%20of%20Syed%20Taqi%20Mir%20and%20terminated%20at%20Shah%20Baqar%20Ka%20Takia.%20Among%20its%20organisers%20were%20Syed%20Ali%20Mir%2C%20Syed%20Taqi%20Mir%2C%20and%20Syed%20Mujataba%20Hussain%20but%20they%20all%20got%20lost%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20Partition%20and%20post-Partition%20brutalities.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123721%2F01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221131%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123721%2F01.jpg%201131w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123721%2F01-300x240.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123721%2F01-1024x819.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673369%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22905%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOnce%20a%20property%20owned%20by%20the%20Muslim%20residents%20of%20Mohalla%20Peer%20Damadiya%2C%20ruins%20of%20a%20home%20that%20has%20been%20converted%20into%20a%20cattle%20shed.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Noon-gola%20locality%2C%20which%20has%20now%20been%20renamed%20as%20Nand-gola%2C%20was%20once%20the%20residence%20of%20the%20family%20of%20Lutfullah%20Khan%20Sadiq%2C%20the%20Nawab%20of%20Panipat.%20Their%20family%20graveyard%20along%20with%20the%20tombs%20of%20Shah%20Qasim%20Ali%2C%20Shah%20Lillahi%2C%20and%20the%20graves%20of%20Shah%20Alimullah%20and%20Nawab%20Mohammad%20Hassan%20Khan%20(from%20the%20family%20of%20Nawab%20Bakhsi-ul-Mulk%20Hedayat%20Ali%20Khan%20Bahadur%20Asad%20Jung)%20were%20situated%C2%A0%20here%2C%20but%20all%20these%20are%20now%20undetectable.%20Neither%20is%20there%20any%20trace%20of%20the%20mosque%20of%20Isa%20Khan%20Rifat.%20This%20quarter%20housed%20the%20Imambara%20of%20Imtiaz%20and%20Sarfaraz%20Khan%2C%20who%20were%20the%20sons%20of%20Shakir%20Khan%2C%20which%20was%20later%20managed%20by%20Hedayat%20Ali%20Khan%20(Sadr-E-Aala%20of%20Bihar)%20and%20his%20descendants%20Abdul%20Shakur%20Khan%20and%20Nazeer%20Hussain%20Shaiq%2C%20an%20eminent%20Urdu%20poet).%20Shakir%20Khan%20organised%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDuldul%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(replica%20of%20Imam%20Hussain%E2%80%99s%20horse)%20procession%20which%20was%20quite%20famous%20in%20the%20city.%20When%20the%20country%20was%20divided%20in%201947%2C%20all%20these%20families%20had%20to%20leave%20their%20ancestral%20place%2C%20deserting%20it%20forever%20and%20now%2C%20there%20are%20no%20traces%20of%20their%20houses%20or%20the%20said%20Imambaras.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20who%20stayed%20back%20in%20their%20mohallas%20after%201947%20had%20to%20suffer%20multiple%20riots%20including%20those%20occurring%20in%201990%20and%201992%20which%20forced%20them%20to%20leave%20permanently.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20their%20properties%20were%20looted%20and%20desecrated.%20There%20are%20innumerable%20properties%20lying%20abandoned%20and%20encroached%20in%20Patna%20which%20once%20belonged%20to%20the%20Muslims.%20Those%20who%20are%20still%20living%20in%20Patna%20are%20unable%20to%20gain%20their%20properties%20back%20owing%20to%20a%C2%A0%20sense%20of%20fear%20and%20lack%20of%20community%20members%20around%20them.%20It%20is%20a%20general%20perception%20across%20the%20city%20that%20all%20the%20abandoned%20Muslim%20properties%20are%20in%20such%20a%20state%20because%20their%20owners%20migrated%20to%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20border%2C%20however%2C%20this%20is%20not%20always%20true.%20This%20opinion%20is%20on%20a%20rise%20these%20days%20giving%20ample%20opportunities%20to%20land%20sharks%20to%20grab%20such%20properties.%20This%20is%20a%C2%A0%20brunt%20of%20Partition%20that%20the%20minority%20is%20still%20facing%20in%20Patna%20and%20other%20similar%20places.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNoon-gola%2C%20Mohalla%20Peer%20Damadiya%2C%20Zulqadar%20Bagh%2C%20Simli%2C%20Nagla%2C%20Bangla%2C%20Abdurrahmanpur%2C%20Nooruddin%20Ganj%2C%20Rakab%20Ganj%2C%20Nawab%20Ganj%2C%20Sadara%2C%20Jamnapur%2C%20Begumpur%2C%20Deedarganj%2C%20Dalhatta%2C%20Shah%20Bahor%20Ka%20Takiya%2C%20Meer%20Jawan%20Ki%20Chawni%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20Mohallas%20were%20densely%20populated%20by%20the%20Muslim%20families%20before%20the%C2%A0Partition%20took%20place%20in%201947.%20But%2C%20today%20you%20can%20easily%20count%20their%20numbers%20which%20won%E2%80%99t%20exceed%2040%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20Anwar%20Alam%2C%20the%20last%20Muslim%20resident%20of%20Noon-gola%2C%20who%20bid%20farewell%20to%20the%20area%20after%20the%201992%20riots%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20post-Partition%20riots%20that%20the%20country%20witnessed.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F08232004%2FIMG_20191106_0004.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22DO%20NOT%20USE%20AGAIN%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F08232004%2FIMG_20191106_0004.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F08232004%2FIMG_20191106_0004-300x202.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F08232004%2FIMG_20191106_0004-1024x688.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-411882%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22806%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHindu%20activists%20climb%20the%20dome%20of%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%20which%20was%20quickly%20demolished.%20Archival%20photograph%3A%20Sondeep%20Shankar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20family%20was%20the%20last%20Muslim%20family%20in%20Noon-gola.%20People%20started%20migrating%20much%20before%20the%20Partition%20was%20announced.%20It%20was%20the%20riots%20of%201946%20which%20made%20them%20believe%20that%20the%20quarter%20inhabited%20by%20their%20forefathers%20for%20centuries%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20safe%20for%20them%20anymore.%20My%20grandfather%20too%20wanted%20to%20move%20out%2C%20but%20his%20Hindu%20neighbours%20asked%20him%20to%20stay.%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20Noon-gola%2C%20and%20everything%20was%20almost%20fine%20until%20the%20riots%20in%201990%20and%20then%20in%201992%20%E2%80%93%20the%20year%20when%20Babri%20mosque%20was%20demolished%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%E2%80%9D%20Alam%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20concluded%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20here%20in%201990%2C%20but%20in%201992%20the%20atmosphere%20had%20changed.%20The%20residents%20who%20had%20asked%20my%20grandfather%20to%20stay%2C%20swearing%20on%20their%20relations%20and%20brotherhood%20were%20dead%20and%20so%20were%20their%20promises.%20I%20was%20attacked%20in%20the%20same%20area%20where%20I%20was%20born.%20Around%2020%20people%20heckled%20me%20on%20the%20streets%3B%20though%20I%20somehow%20managed%20to%20escape%20and%20took%20shelter%20in%20Rabbu%20Sahab%E2%80%99s%20clinic%2C%20which%20was%20blown%20up%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20left.%20That%20was%20my%20last%20day%20there.%20I%20sold%20everything%20and%20moved%20to%20a%20safer%20place%2C%20near%20the%20western%20gate%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%201992%20came%20as%20a%20substantial%20nightmare%20for%20the%20persecuted%20minority%20in%20Patna%2C%20the%20statistics%20of%20violence%20were%20no%20less%20fierce%20in%201990%20%E2%80%93%20which%20witnessed%20the%20bombing%20on%20the%20sacred%20Simli%20Khanqah%20and%20the%20house%20of%20Sattar%20Sahab.%20This%20year%20also%20saw%20the%20brutal%20murder%20of%20Afzal%2C%20a%20young%20man%2C%20near%20Dhawalpura%2C%20once%20a%20Muslim%20hub.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKamaal%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Nagla%2C%20said%20that%20there%20were%20a%20few%20families%20who%20decided%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20area%20despite%20all%20odds%2C%20and%20they%20suffered%20the%20most%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time%2C%20adding%20that%E2%80%9C%20there%20were%20friends%20as%20well%E2%80%9D.%20He%20remembered%20how%20he%2C%20along%20with%20his%20friend%20Sanjay%20Pandit%2C%20used%20to%20wipe%20out%20the%20hateful%20slogans%20smeared%20on%20the%20walls%20in%20the%20area%20asking%20the%20Hindus%20to%20march%20to%20Ayodhya%20on%20December%206%20to%20demolish%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201992.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilar%20fate%20struck%20Qasai-bada%2C%20also%20a%20prominent%20Muslim%20vicinity%20near%20Begumpur.%20Still%2C%20there%20is%20a%20mosque%20which%20is%20the%20last%20surviving%20symbol%20of%20the%20community%20which%20once%20resided%20here.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123850%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-12.37.59-PM.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221048%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123850%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-12.37.59-PM.jpg%201048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123850%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-12.37.59-PM-262x300.jpg%20262w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17123850%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-12.37.59-PM-894x1024.jpg%20894w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673370%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMosque%20of%20Munshi%20Kazim%20Ali%20as%20seen%20from%20the%20Ashok%20Rajpath.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQuite%20close%20to%20the%20former%20residence%20of%20Shad%20is%20the%20Mosque%20of%20Munshi%20Kazim%20Ali%20%E2%80%93%20a%20survivor%20of%20the%20horrors%20of%20post-Partition%20migration.%20Ali%20had%20constructed%20this%20mosque%20in%201825%2C%20unaware%20that%20it%20would%20be%20encroached%20upon%20and%20desecrated%20by%20the%20majority%20population%20in%20the%20future.%20The%20mosque%20was%20turned%20into%20a%20cattle%20shed%20by%20a%20local%20milkman.%20It%20was%20only%20because%20of%20the%20efforts%20of%20the%20neighbouring%20Muslims%20of%20mohalla%20Batau-Kuan%20that%20after%20several%20years%20of%20scuffle%20and%20struggle%2C%20the%20structure%20was%20recently%20revived%20as%20a%20mosque.%20Despite%20all%20these%20hardships%20Ali%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20grave%20could%20not%20be%20rescued%2C%20and%20as%20per%20the%20locals%2C%20it%20is%20still%20situated%20inside