merican%20Republican%20presidential%20aspirant%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy%20has%20vowed%20to%20%26quot%3Bgut%26quot%3B%20the%20lottery-based%20system%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20meritocratic%20admission%20if%20he%20wins%20the%20race%20to%20the%20White%20House%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20visa%2C%20the%20much-sought-after%20among%20Indian%20IT%20professionals%2C%20is%20a%20non-immigrant%20visa%20that%20allows%20US%20companies%20to%20employ%20foreign%20workers%20in%20speciality%20occupations%20that%20require%20theoretical%20or%20technical%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20companies%20depend%20on%20it%20to%20hire%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20employees%20each%20year%20from%20countries%20like%20India%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Ramaswamy%20himself%20has%20used%20the%20visa%20programme%2029%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202018%20through%202023%2C%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20approved%2029%20applications%20for%20Ramaswamy's%20former%20company%2C%20Roivant%20Sciences%2C%20to%20hire%20employees%20under%20H-1B%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20H-1B%20system%20is%20%26quot%3Bbad%20for%20everyone%20involved%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Ramaswamy%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20Politico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lottery%20system%20needs%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20actual%20meritocratic%20admission.%20It's%20a%20form%20of%20indentured%20servitude%20that%20only%20accrues%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20company%20that%20sponsored%20an%20H-1B%20immigrant.%20I'll%20gut%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20US%20needs%20to%20eliminate%20chain-based%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20come%20as%20family%20members%20are%20not%20the%20meritocratic%20immigrants%20who%20make%20skills-based%20contributions%20to%20this%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Ramaswamy%20stepped%20down%20as%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Roivant%20in%20February%202021%2C%20but%20remained%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20company's%20board%20of%20directors%20until%20February%20this%20year%20when%20he%20announced%20his%20presidential%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20March%2031%2C%20the%20company%20and%20its%20subsidiaries%20had%20904%20full-time%20employees%2C%20including%20825%20in%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20its%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20mismatch%20in%20the%20Republican%20presidential%20hopeful's%20policy%20stance%20and%20his%20past%20business%20practices%2C%20press%20secretary%20Tricia%20McLaughlin%20said%20the%20role%20of%20a%20policymaker%20%26quot%3Bis%20to%20do%20what's%20right%20for%20a%20country%20overall%3A%20the%20system%20is%20broken%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20fixed.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVivek%20believes%20that%20regulations%20overseeing%20the%20U.S.%20energy%20sector%20are%20badly%20broken%2C%20but%20he%20still%20uses%20water%20and%20electricity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20same.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Ramaswamy%2C%20who%20is%20himself%20the%20child%20of%20immigrants%2C%20has%20captured%20headlines%20for%20his%20restrictionist%20immigration%20policy%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20he%20would%20use%20military%20force%20to%20secure%20the%20border%2C%20and%20that%20he%20would%20deport%20US-born%20children%20of%20undocumented%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EH-1B%20visas%20are%20highly%20sought%20after%2C%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20these%20workers%20continues%20to%20increase.%20For%20fiscal%20year%202021%2C%20US%20businesses%20submitted%20780%2C884%20applications%20for%20just%2085%2C000%20available%20slots%2C%20jumping%20by%20more%20than%2060%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Ramaswamy%20acknowledged%20his%20own%20experience%20with%20immigration%20during%20his%20opening%20remarks%20at%20the%20first%20Republican%20debate%20in%20Milwaukee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20came%20to%20this%20country%20with%20no%20money%2040%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20found%20multi-billion-dollar%20companies.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Ramaswamy's%20stance%20on%20H-1B%20visas%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20the%202016%20Trump%20campaign%2C%20when%20then-candidate%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20who%20has%20also%20hired%20a%20number%20of%20foreign%20workers%20under%20H-1B%20visas%20for%20his%20businesses%2C%20took%20a%20hardline%20stance%20on%20these%20foreign%20workers%20before%20later%20softening%20his%20rhetoric.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20president%2C%20Trump%20temporarily%20suspended%20new%20work%20visas%20and%20blocked%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20foreign%20workers%20from%20US%20employment%2C%20as%20part%20of%20his%20sweeping%20effort%20to%20limit%20the%20number%20of%20immigrants%20coming%20into%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20the%20US%20gives%2065%2C000%20H-1B%20visas%20which%20are%20open%20to%20all%20and%2020%2C000%20to%20those%20with%20advanced%20US%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Indian-American%20Congressman%20Raja%20Krishnamoorthi%20introduced%20a%20bill%20proposing%20to%20double%20the%20annual%20intake%20of%20highly%20skilled%20foreign%20workers%20on%20H-1B%20work%20visas%20coveted%20by%20Indian%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20also%20seeks%20to%20double%20the%20number%20of%20H-1B%20visas%20available%20annually%20from%2065%2C000%20to%20130%2C000%20to%20allow%20American%20employers%2C%20including%20in%20critical%20technology%20sectors%2C%20to%20draw%20the%20best%20talent%20from%20around%20the%20world.%20Currently%2C%20nearly%20three-fourths%20of%20H-1B%20visas%20go%20to%20Indian%20professionals.%3Cbr%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694934840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.nd