C%22%3EPesaha%20appam%20eaten%20on%20Maundy%20Thursday%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20X%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FKeralaTourism%2Fstatus%2F1643869623551422466%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKerala%20Tourism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20unleavened%20bread%20prepared%20without%20using%20yeast%20and%20commonly%20eaten%20on%20Maundy%20Thursday%20(%3Cem%3EPesaha%20Vyazhacha%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20book%20tells%20of%20how%20it%20is%20made%20with%20great%20solemnity%20by%20the%20women%20of%20the%20household.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F326173%2Forigins-of-iconic-indian-dishes-loved-across-the-world-food-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20bread%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20cooked%20by%20placing%20a%20cross%20made%20from%20the%20palm%20leaf%20received%20on%20Palm%20Sunday.%20In%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20male%20head%20of%20the%20family%20breaks%20the%20bread%20after%20prayers%20and%20shares%20it%20with%20his%20family%20to%20commemorate%20the%20Last%20Supper.%20The%20bread%20is%20eaten%20with%20a%20jaggery%20sauce%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20notes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Ariputtu%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2015th%20century%20when%20the%20Portuguese%20entered%20Kerala%2C%20they%20brought%20with%20them%20spices%2C%20potatoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20etc.%20One%20of%20the%20foods%20they%20%E2%80%9Cinvented%E2%80%9D%2C%20shares%20Tanya%20in%20her%20book%2C%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Eputtu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20steamed%20rice%20cake).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20talks%20of%20how%20the%20%3Cem%3Eputtu%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20originally%20made%20in%20bamboo%20steamers%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325105%2Fhyderabad-entrepreneur-raju-bhupati-makes-affordable-troo-good-millet-snacks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoconut%20shells%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20has%20now%20shifted%20to%20more%20user-friendly%20metal%20%3Cem%3Eputtu%3C%2Fem%3E-makers.%20In%20contrast%20to%20the%20previously%20used%20%3Cem%3Eoralus%20%3C%2Fem%3E(granite%20tools)%2C%20mill-ground%20rice%20is%20now%20used.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Chemeen%20Pada%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shrimp%20pickle%2C%20a%20staple%20in%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20household%2C%20is%20an%20ode%20to%20the%20Portuguese%20tradition%20of%20pickling%20meats%20in%20vinegar.%20In%20fact%2C%20as%20Tanya%20writes%2C%20vinegar%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20foods%20brought%20to%20Kerala%20during%20the%20colonisation%20in%20the%2015th%20century.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Portuguese%20used%20vinegar%20extensively%20in%20their%20food%3B%20especially%20to%20preserve%20salted%20meats%20with%20paprika%20and%20garlic%20which%20were%20stored%20in%20large%20barrels%20during%20their%20voyages%20in%20ships%20to%20lands%20afar.%20This%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20quick%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F324582%2Fshashikala-sanadhya-gives-indian-food-cooking-lessons-for-foreign-tourists-in-udaipur%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esavouring%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20fried%20in%20oil%2C%20close%20to%20the%20meat%20pickle%20famously%20relished%20in%20Kerala%20today.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Kazhal%20Kothiyathu%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Latin%20Catholic%20minced%20liver%20fry%20recipe%20prepared%20by%20Tanya%E2%80%99s%20grandmother%20differs%20from%20other%20community%20recipes%20in%20terms%20of%20preparation.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20unusual%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Tanya%2C%20who%20noticed%20how%20cooking%20styles%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3